devdoc.author: EL BACHRA
devdoc.details: This contract manages property ownership and diagnostics requests for properties. It allows property owners to register, certified diagnosticians to create diagnostic reports, and property factory contracts to create and transfer property ownership. It also includes a registration fee, and events for property and diagnostic creation, owner and diagnostician registration and certification, and fund withdrawals.

params.diagnosticianAddress: The address of the diagnostician requesting verification.

params.property: The address of the property for which the diagnostic was created.
params.tokenId: The unique identifier of the created diagnostic.

params.diagnostician: The address of the diagnostician assigned to perform the diagnostic.
params.propertyAddress: The address of the property for which the diagnostic is requested.
params.propertyOwner: The address of the property owner who requested the diagnostic.
params.requestId: The unique identifier of the diagnostic request.

params.propertyAddress: The string representation of the property address for which the diagnostic is requested.
params.propertyOwner: The address of the property owner who requested the diagnostic.
params.requestId: The unique identifier of the diagnostic request.

params.diagnosticianAddress: The address of the certified diagnostician.
The address of the diagnostician whose certification is revoked.

params.account: The address of the account that withdrew the funds.

params.ownerAddress: The address of the registered property owner.

params.property: The address of the created property.

params.propertyFactoryAddress: The address of the PropertyFactory contract.

createDiagnostic(uint256,string,string,u.details: Function that allows certified diagnosticians to create a diagnostic. The function checks if the requestId is valid and if a diagnostic request exists for the given requestId. It then calls the createDiagnostic function of the PropertyFactory contract, marks the request as completed, and emits a DiagnosticCreated event.

params._documentHash: The IPFS hash of the diagnostic document.
params._expiryDate: The expiry date of the diagnostic in UNIX timestamp format.
params._tokenURI: The URI of the diagnostic token.
params.requestId: The identifier of the diagnostic request.

createProperty(string,string).details: Function that allows property owners to create a new property. The function calls the createProperty function of the PropertyFactory contract and emits a PropertyCreated event.

returns._0: The address of the created property.

getDiagnosticHash(address,uint256).details: Function that retrieves the IPFS hash of a diagnostic associated with a property and a token ID.

params.property: The address of the property associated with the diagnostic.
params.tokenId: The identifier of the diagnostic token.

returns._0: The IPFS hash of the diagnostic document.

getDiagnosticRequests(address).details: Function that returns an array of DiagnosticRequest structs for a certified diagnostician.

params._diagnostician: The address of the certified diagnostician.

getUserProperties().details: Function that returns an array of Property structs for the calling user.

myself().details: Function that returns the role and certification status of the caller. The possible roles are SmartContractOwner, PropertyOwner, CertifiedDiagnostician, UncertifiedDiagnostician, and NoRole.

returns._0: UserInfo memory object containing the role and certification status of the caller.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

registerOwner().details: Function that allows users to register as a property owner. The function checks if the sent value is greater than or equal to the registration fee and if the sender is not already a registered owner. If both conditions are met, the sender is registered as a property owner and the OwnerRegistered event is emitted.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

requestDiagnostic(address,address).details: Function that allows property owners to request a diagnostic. The function creates a new DiagnosticRequest struct, stores it in the diagnosticRequests mapping, and emits a DiagnosticRequested event.

params._diagnostician: The address of the certified diagnostician.
params._propertyAddress: The address of the property to be diagnosed.

requestVerification(string,string).details: Function that allows uncertified diagnosticians to request verification. The function checks if the sender is not already certified, and if so, stores their information and sets their pendingVerification status to true. It also emits an AskedVerification event.

params._siret: The SIRET identifier of the diagnostician.

revokeDiagnosticianVerification(address).details: Function that revokes the verification status of a diagnostician. Only the smart contract owner can call this function. The function sets the isCertified status of the diagnostician to false and emits a DiagnosticianRevoked event.

params._diagnostician: The address of the diagnostician whose verification status is to be revoked.

setRegistrationFee(uint256).details: Function that allows the smart contract owner to set a new registration fee.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

transferOwnership(address,address,uint25.details: Function that allows property owners to transfer ownership of a diagnostic token. The function calls the transferOwnership function of the PropertyFactory contract.

params._property: The address of the property associated with the diagnostic token.
params._to: The address to transfer the ownership of the token to.
params._tokenId: The identifier of the diagnostic token.

verifyDiagnostician(address).details: Function that allows the smart contract owner to verify a diagnostician. The function checks if the diagnostician is not already certified, and if so, sets their isCertified status to true and pendingVerification status to false. It also emits a DiagnosticianCertified event.

params._diagnostician: The address of the diagnostician to be verified.

withdrawFunds(address).details: Function that allows the smart contract owner to withdraw the accumulated funds. The function transfers the contract balance to the provided recipient address and emits a FundsWithdrawn event.

params._recipient: The address of the recipient to receive the funds.
